# Copy to deploy/hermes-sidecar.runtime.env and point HERMES_SIDECAR_RUNTIME_ENV_FILE at it.
#
# This file is injected into the real Hermes sidecar runtime container with compose `env_file:`.
# Put runtime-specific credentials/config here.
#
# The proxy variables (HTTP_PROXY / HTTPS_PROXY / NO_PROXY) are injected by
# deploy/compose.hermes-sidecar.override.yaml, so you usually do not need
# to repeat them here unless your image expects additional custom names.
# That compose override also mounts the exported proxy CA certificate at
# /opt/agent-auditor/certs/mitmproxy-ca-cert.pem and injects
# AGENT_AUDITOR_PROXY_CA_CERT with the same in-container path.
# Hermes sidecar runtime proxy/cert contract when you keep env-based injection:
# - proxy route: http://127.0.0.1:8080
# - no-proxy set: hostd,localhost,127.0.0.1
# - mounted CA path: /opt/agent-auditor/certs/mitmproxy-ca-cert.pem
# If the Hermes launcher or bundled tools need explicit lowercase proxy aliases,
# mirror the injected proxy route here too:
# http_proxy=http://127.0.0.1:8080
# https_proxy=http://127.0.0.1:8080
# no_proxy=hostd,localhost,127.0.0.1
# If the Hermes image uses app-level or client-specific trust variables instead of
# the OS trust store, uncomment the ones it respects and point them at that mounted cert path.
# NODE_EXTRA_CA_CERTS=/opt/agent-auditor/certs/mitmproxy-ca-cert.pem
# REQUESTS_CA_BUNDLE=/opt/agent-auditor/certs/mitmproxy-ca-cert.pem
# SSL_CERT_FILE=/opt/agent-auditor/certs/mitmproxy-ca-cert.pem
# CURL_CA_BUNDLE=/opt/agent-auditor/certs/mitmproxy-ca-cert.pem
# GIT_SSL_CAINFO=/opt/agent-auditor/certs/mitmproxy-ca-cert.pem

# Example placeholders only — replace with the actual variables your Hermes image expects.
# GOOGLE_OAUTH_ACCESS_TOKEN=
# HERMES_CONFIG_PATH=/workspace/.hermes/config.yaml
